Reliable quality fast food is hard to find on the Strip, and most of it is Airport-style scandalously overpriced.
Planet Hollywood's Earl of Sandwich is one of the very few deals, a Quizno's-style counter that's actually cheaper than the Quizno's on the Strip (and yes, better).
Solid meat-combo toasted sandwiches, and very good tomato soup (better than many places that brag about their tomato soup).
Very surprising that the chain hasn't expanded more here...wonder if PH has some sort of exclusive deal?

