) AND STILL good at 5PM the next day before a night of drinking.
The key is the quality of the bread, the meat, and sauces.
The competition needs to take a page out of Earl of Sandwich's playbook - quality over quantity.
Generous portions of meat but NOT too much meat to overdo it.
Not like those other sandwich shops that just serve you the side of an animal piled up between two small slices of bread.
Earl of Sandwich serves the perfect amounts of meat, sauce and veggies.
The process is so streamline - the line may seem long but they have fulfillment down to a science so it moves fast.
Place your order, listen for your number - done!
A word of advice - if you are a big eater - order two sandwiches.
I'm not saying they're small by any means - but they are soo good and go down so easily - you'll be craving another.
TRUST me.

