Every time I come to Vegas, I really look forward to these sandwiches.
They're simple, they're affordable, they're open late and they're delicious!
I was first introduced to these sandwiches when my family and I were exploring Plant Hollywood's Miracle Mile shops and the then "new" PH Westgate condos.
We stopped by here after one of the hostess recommended it and I've been a fan ever since.
I enjoy the variety they offer, especially on their signature hot sandwich menu.
I've had a couple and they are all tasty.
These are a couple of my favorites, depending on what food mood I am in.
For a tasty well-rounded sandwich, I'd go with The Full Montagu (Freshly Roasted Beef, Turkey, Aged Swiss & Sharp Cheddar Cheese, Lettuce, Roma Tomatoes & the Earl's Mustard Sauce).
For something tangy and sweet, I'd go with the Caribbean Jerk Chicken (Grilled Chicken, Roasted Red & Banana Peppers & Spicy Jerk Sauce).
