First off, let me just say, I am not the biggest fan of sandwiches.
Too many times, there has been uneven ratios of filling to bread, fillings sliding all over the place, falling out, leaving you with a mess of a sandwich, and you have to eat the rest in sections.
But after trying a sandwich from this place, it is hands down one of the best hot sandwiches I've ever had.
I've converted many people because of this place.
Stationed near the Hawaiian Tropics place in Planet Hollywood, this place looks like your typical cafeteria style sandwich place.
The menu has your usual tasty array of different types of sandwiches, from Meatball sandwiches and Tuna Melts to interesting ones like Caribbean Jerk Chicken.
You order your sandwich, pay for it, and they hand you a buzzer for when the sandwich is ready.
Everything is made to order.
As you receive your sandwich, it is wrapped neatly in a foil paper, nice and toasty, fresh from the counter.
You unwrap the sandwich, and it just looks like a normal unassuming sandwich, but in that first bite, you wonder where this sandwich has been all your life.
It has the perfect ratio of filling vs bread, the bread is crunchy on the outside and light and fluffy on the inside.
And each bite after is sandwich perfection, having just the right amount so that nothing spills out of your sandwich as you are eating it, making it the perfect sandwich experience.
Oh and if you still have room after the sandwich, try their homemade brownies.
Chocolate heaven.
Don't forget to get a nice cold glass of milk to go with it.

