The only sandwich I tried was their Tuna Melt but it here but it had to be the best Tuna Melt I've ever had...so good in fact, that I had to go back again for another one!
The bread was perfectly toasted so that it was crunchy but still also soft on the inside, it had a generous amount of Tuna with just the right amount of cheese so that it's not overly greasy.
My other girlfriends ordered some of the other sandwiches like The Earl and Cannonball and they raved that those were just as yummy too.
One sandwich is pretty filling by itself but if you have room I'd also recommend their potato soup.
It's tasty and hearty and doesn't taste processed or canned like some soups I've tried at other sandwich places.
To top it off, their service is really quick too.
