The sandwiches are a decent size - one plus a side will definitely be enough to tide you over throughout the night.
If I remember correctly (those hangovers don't come outta nowhere people!
), we had the Italian, BLT and the Full Montagu (over a two night period) and I believe the Italian was my favorite.
I really like the potato salad here too.
The line does go fast... seriously.
And once you order, it's only minutes till your chow is ready to go.
I'd give an extra point if they had cold sandwiches.
Sorry, that's just how I like 'em.
Otherwise this is a solid spot for a late night snack.

