I'm going from strictly memory of my Earl of Sandwich experience.
My fat Hawaiian friend recommended this spot and after building his creditability with the Pizzeria @ The Cosmopolitan, I gave in.
Earl's is pretty easy to find and is right across from the Sugar Factory.
The sandwich shop was pretty busy, but it could of been the holiday, 4th of July.
The menu is extensive and consists of hot sandwiches, salads & wraps, desserts, breakfast items, and beverages and smoothies.
I opted for a hot sandwich, more specifically the Caribbean Jerk Chicken.
The sandwich is subtle and includes grilled chicken, roasted red & banana peppers, and their signature spicy jerk sauce.
The sandwich was mouth watering delicious.
The chicken was nicely grilled and seasoned.
The lettuce, tomato, and peppers gave it that crunch, and their jerk sauce gave it that kick without overwhelming the overall taste.
The food was awesome, but I do suggest ordering a large or two sandwiches, as I was left somewhat unfilled after my regular sized sandwich.
It's no five star sandwich but it's damn close.

