Went there for lunch, line was about 50 people long.
Ordered the Hawaiian BBQ sandwich.
Bread, chicken, ham, pinapple and Hawaiian BBQ sauce.
The sandwich was a good size-- about the size of a large Quizno's sub.
The meat inside the sandwich was tasty-- especially the rolls of ham.
They overwhelmed my sandwich with their Hawaiian BBQ sauce.
