We came to Vegas for the weekend and in the process of walking around, became hungry, so we checked out yelp for some options.
Lo and behold, Earl of Sandwich came up and with so many reviews and a good overall rating, we decided to check it out.
We (my girlfriend and I), split the Caprese salad and settled on the club and the Italian for hot sandwiches.
The salad wasn't bad, the cheese was fresh and it had a good taste overall, but compared to the ones we make at home it wasn't bad.
