I wasn't sure about it being classified as a "hot sandwich" on the menu when I ordered it (not really a fan of warm tomatoes) but it was really tasty.
It was warmed just enough to crisp the bread and make the mozzarella even more tender.
My sister loved her Earl's Club (turkey, bacon, cheese) as well.
For the two sandwiches, two cookies, and two sodas, our bill was $21 which is not a bad price at all, especially since we left satisfied and full.
Since this is such a popular place, seating can be tricky to find, so be patient.
Thankfully it's just a sandwich place, so turnover at the tables is pretty good as long as people don't linger once they are done.
For a reasonable priced and good lunch in Vegas, Earl of Sandwich is a great option.

