For a strip sandwich shop, this place is probably the choice if you're near it.
The sandwiches are heated little masterpieces.
They are priced well, surprisingly, and very satisfying.
Although, only satisfying when you don't think about them too much.
They are skimpy on the meat, and they only have white bread as a choice, but still - for some reason, it's really good.
Maybe it's the whole baking process they send their sandwiches through.
It works wonders (I think Subway caught onto this with the whole "toasted" movement).
The bottom line is - these are tasty sandwiches that won't make you cringe with a typical strip price.
This is a pleasant surprise to anyone who buys food from a hotel spot.
