the premiere hot sandwich, Earl's has built an empire with these yellow bricks (of sandwiches).
the location is amazingly convenient (which is one of the reasons why they get so much foot traffic).
i've seen their lines stretch at east 30 or 40 people deep- breakfast, lunch, or dinner, the wait is well worth it.
their ordering system is highly efficient (which is a relief), and although there may come a time where there isn't enough room in their dining area to enjoy your sandwich there, it's still just as satisfying if you take it to go and bring it back up to your room at the Westgate Towers or other nearby hotel.
the tuna melt and hawaiian sandwiches are my favorite, but the jerk chicken or montagus are also great.
much like the buffets, Earl's is a 'must try' for those enjoying Las Vegas for the first time.
you'll find yourself always going back on subsequent trips to enjoy one of their hot sandwiches.
and it's open 24 hours = makes a great breakfast or late night/post-clubbing meal as well.
-civilities.

