I am in awe of the limited options of 24 hour places to eat in Sin City!
We stayed at the Aria this past weekend and our only option was the Aria Cafe, which was open 24 hours but was a bit on the pricier end.
We decided to take the tram over to the Bellagio and walk to PH to dig into Earl of Sandwich, which is also open 24 hours.
Sandwiches will run you about $6.45 here.
They're made-to-order, so they're toasty and warm.
Plus, the bread is out of this world and the sandwich is a great fix at basically any time of the day.
The lines move pretty fast, also.
I opted to get the Original (which is basically what I get every time), and it doesn't disappoint.
Use the horseradish/grey poupon sauce on the table for a little kick.
Thanks for a fast, delicious, and cheap option... and for being open when everything else isn't!

