Definitely a must when visiting Vegas!
You really can't go wrong with Earl.
It's cheap ($6-7 for any sandwich), open 24/7, and there are lots of options to choose from.
My favorites are the holiday turkey (it's Thanksgiving in a sandwich!
) and the Original 1762.
The bread makes all the difference!
It is perfectly toasted.
At the other Earl locations, you can choose from white or wheat bread, but at the Vegas location, they only have white available (probably to speed up the ordering process since lines can get long).
As many others have said, it's perfect for lunch, after a drunken night out, or a quick snack.
If you're especially hungry, you might want to order two.
The lines can get a little long sometimes, but it's totally worth it.

