Let me preface this review by saying that I am not that big on sandwiches.
Sometimes I feel sandwiches are something you make at home, not really worth going out of your way for.
Then, I had a chance to test Earl of Sandwich.
This is my fav sandwich spot hands down.
I am so glad they built on in downtown Disney which is a lot closer to me than Vegas.
I usually get a hot sandwich and the tuna is so good!
The way they grill the hot sandwiches is perfect.
While, I don't frequent the shops at PH when I go to Vegas, I would recommend trying out this place if you are at the shops and just want something quick.

We always end up coming here on any trip to Vegas!
Where else can you get a yummy meal for $6-$7 on the strip??
I usually get the full montagu, though it really just depends what kind of a mood I'm in!
There's always usually a line, but I've gotten lucky during odd hours (in-between meals) where the line was fairly short, and it moves fairly quickly for the most part too.
I love that their sandwiches are so warm and toasty right when you get them, and they're also the perfect size for me (though admittedly I don't eat that much!
)  They've got tables & seating right there too, usually not too hard to find a seat because people finish eating pretty quickly.
Anywho, definitely worth a visit if you're in Vegas, and the biggest money-saver yet!
A Vegas rarity.

